<subSubSection id="644F913C7A4B44737B582BA70F6AC235" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" type="chemistry">
<paragraph id="B3091B3CC3E4A4E7F401A5939846A6BD" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">Chemistry.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C999D9735E49245C33ED229AD83BAA89" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">Upper cortex K-, C-, P-, medulla K + yellow, C-, P-; usnic and placodiolic acids.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="DBA9211EE3A8A2E83287E78897E2E42F" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" type="ecology">
<paragraph id="87B41855E1A02E29DE023362EFA98DEE" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">Ecology and distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6F9DE27DA8D4A915E158621C048A01CF" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">Growing on rock in arid environments at elevations of 984-2100 m. Previously only known from Yunnan Prov., here reported as new to Sichuan Prov., China.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="AC16AC2D13DF4FB9BDF6BF6B9D821458" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" type="notes">
<paragraph id="A4D2F1F7A1370CB428A56A42DBF21DA6" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5CBE99B662C4CC64329269DCBC4D5B22" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">
The isotype grows on quartzitic rock ca. 2 cm across, containing several intact apothecia. The spore size of &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="4C96BAA22875896A7BBE7EED0B1965EB" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Stereocaulaceae" genus="Squamarina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Squamarina callichroa" order="Lecanorales" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="callichroa">
<emphasis id="2EBCFA631537B80948899D4987D1B617" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">Squamarina callichroa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot;, given in the protologue, is 15-20 
<normalizedToken id="B197354327F142B8EC8D9104DFC1A436" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
8-9 
<normalizedToken id="668FC7478763DC7121C9D7BB604B45AF" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
(
<bibRefCitation id="71832958EF97068CA84173AC1757966D" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-7091-4178-6_1" author="Zahlbruckner, A" journalOrPublisher="Springer, Vienna" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" refId="B19" refString="Zahlbruckner, A, 1930. Lichenes. In: Handel-Mazzetti H (Ed.) Symbolae Sinicae 3. J. Springer, Vienna, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-7091-4178-6_1" title="Lichenes. In: Handel-Mazzetti H (Ed.) Symbolae Sinicae 3. J." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-7091-4178-6_1" year="1930">Zahlbruckner 1930</bibRefCitation>
); however, 
<bibRefCitation id="21E5DE0CFEDC455F974F612FDBB9F610" author="Poelt, J" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen der Botanischen Staatssammlung Muechen" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" pagination="411 - 589" refId="B15" refString="Poelt, J, 1958. Die lobaten Arten der Flechtengattung Lecanora Ach. sensu ampl. in der Holarktis. Mitteilungen der Botanischen Staatssammlung Muechen 2 (19-20): 411 - 589" title="Die lobaten Arten der Flechtengattung Lecanora Ach. sensu ampl. in der Holarktis." volume="2" year="1958">Poelt (1958)</bibRefCitation>
measured the spore size of the type material as 11-12 
<normalizedToken id="32ADC0A70FD3D28C20A292BE26F750BD" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
8-9 
<normalizedToken id="F6D84E45FEE2844BE7145E41DA66EAB5" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
. Our measurements of the freshly collected materials, 9.5-13.5 
<normalizedToken id="74D8C75E884DD6F9F659320AA51C5BB5" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
6-9 
<normalizedToken id="E79466484B5325B33BD5AC8AEAF8295A" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, are in accordance with 
<normalizedToken id="0847A519036C672BA004601D287640B1" originalValue="Poelt’s">Poelt's</normalizedToken>
results and the other characteristics, elevation and locality of our collections are more or less identical with the isotype. We did not find any specimens around the type locality having those long ascospores as in the description of the protologue. Therefore, we treat our specimens as &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="1C4D84B18B025BE17BCBF682111DB50A" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Stereocaulaceae" genus="Squamarina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Squamarina callichroa" order="Lecanorales" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="callichroa">
<emphasis id="5DFCA58AA1AC7388D9817FDDAF8B668B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">Squamarina callichroa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot;.This species was originally described as a 
<taxonomicName id="562CC380911E008071229D93E4BAF14F" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Lecanoraceae" genus="Lecanora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Lecanora" order="Lecanorales" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="03BC39DE71FDC07809285821BB36A774" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">Lecanora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="1767E46E3C400056B47008F7E3E61DBD" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-7091-4178-6_1" author="Zahlbruckner, A" journalOrPublisher="Springer, Vienna" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" refId="B19" refString="Zahlbruckner, A, 1930. Lichenes. In: Handel-Mazzetti H (Ed.) Symbolae Sinicae 3. J. Springer, Vienna, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-7091-4178-6_1" title="Lichenes. In: Handel-Mazzetti H (Ed.) Symbolae Sinicae 3. J." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-7091-4178-6_1" year="1930">Zahlbruckner (1930)</bibRefCitation>
and transferred to 
<taxonomicName id="6A599BE38C1F19DE0EF1F44F95F47BF4" authorityName="Poelt" authorityYear="1958" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Stereocaulaceae" genus="Squamarina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Squamarina" order="Lecanorales" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7C09304BBBE9EE329184145C6929989E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">Squamarina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as the type species of the 
<taxonomicName id="DA5F75FDF16132FCA35F191CD852A107" authority="Petroplaca" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Stereocaulaceae" genus="Squamarina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="subsp. section" order="Lecanorales" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="section" section="Petroplaca" species="callichroa" subSpecies="section">section Petroplaca</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="8D75429C17F93E14A99B4ACE04787484" author="Poelt, J" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen der Botanischen Staatssammlung Muechen" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" pagination="411 - 589" refId="B15" refString="Poelt, J, 1958. Die lobaten Arten der Flechtengattung Lecanora Ach. sensu ampl. in der Holarktis. Mitteilungen der Botanischen Staatssammlung Muechen 2 (19-20): 411 - 589" title="Die lobaten Arten der Flechtengattung Lecanora Ach. sensu ampl. in der Holarktis." volume="2" year="1958">Poelt (1958)</bibRefCitation>
. We transfer this species to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="2180D1937D6AB96017306D043A8F1535" authorityName="Zopf" authorityYear="1905" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Lecanoraceae" genus="Rhizoplaca" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Rhizoplaca" order="Lecanorales" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="90A8319228AEA3B65F08B3647AD6D326" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">Rhizoplaca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, primarily based on its nested position within the 
<taxonomicName id="D115143439B50FC4675C98CC4194135C" genus="R." lsidName="R. chrysoleuca" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" rank="species" species="chrysoleuca">
<emphasis id="DB5EC06736B7CD8BC0B55C5E9C7035E8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">R. chrysoleuca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group in the phylogeny (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="D4A86C7E7B5E61A7B8798232A27A5821" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Maximum Likelihood phylogeny of the genus Rhizoplaca and related genera of Lecanoraceae, based on combined nrITS, nrLSU, RPB 1, RPB 2 and mtSSU. ML bootstrap value ≥ 70 % and posterior probabilities ≥ 0.95 from the Bayesian analysis are given adjacent to nodes." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.66.39057.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/403704" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">4</figureCitation>
) and also based on the orange apothecia, the 
<taxonomicName id="6438FB83961FE207FC6EFA68E02A2411" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Lecanoraceae" genus="Lecanora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Lecanora" order="Lecanorales" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8CA1363B5097E157954857A07AD87272" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">Lecanora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-type ascus and the presence of usnic and placodiolic acids. The genus 
<taxonomicName id="1C5E5AB8ED8E7954CE4D2007FB4596A0" authorityName="Zopf" authorityYear="1905" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Lecanoraceae" genus="Rhizoplaca" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Rhizoplaca" order="Lecanorales" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="423D6EB2A565CB68F638990F832C0C7F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">Rhizoplaca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a small genus containing eleven species (
<bibRefCitation id="A83F869805C57C938553E1909C60A735" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1639/0007-2745-119.4.361" author="Luecking, R" journalOrPublisher="The Bryologist" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" pagination="361 - 416" refId="B9" refString="Luecking, R, Hodkinson, BP, Leavitt, SD, 2017. The 2016 classification of lichenized fungi in the Ascomycota and Basidiomycota - Approaching one thousand genera. The Bryologist 119: 361 - 416, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1639/0007-2745-119.4.361" title="The 2016 classification of lichenized fungi in the Ascomycota and Basidiomycota - Approaching one thousand genera." url="https://doi.org/10.1639/0007-2745-119.4.361" volume="119" year="2017">
<normalizedToken id="1124101109FE49D3D37C7C79FD3E9A50" originalValue="Lücking">Luecking</normalizedToken>
et al. 2017
</bibRefCitation>
). We added nine of these species as intergroups to assess the phylogenetic position of 
<taxonomicName id="D4791FEFF17A82108D20499D28FD386B" genus="R." lsidName="R. callichroa" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" rank="species" species="callichroa">
<emphasis id="93E5F7D42992E0B7A354343046156210" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">R. callichroa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the genus. The results show that 
<taxonomicName id="9C2E50C7B76BCB19BF3C09FCE3CFB888" genus="R." lsidName="R. callichroa" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" rank="species" species="callichroa">
<emphasis id="9B03DEE00C3DE9EB199B9B9382AEC942" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">R. callichroa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is sister to 
<taxonomicName id="0AC4D73ABB292DF57783DC55CA5B4EBE" genus="R." lsidName="R. chrysoleuca" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" rank="species" species="chrysoleuca">
<emphasis id="2A4DBF33A89DF84C84A05B5212421085" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">R. chrysoleuca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="8988CFC94CBDFBE0F5D31A005C4251C8" genus="R." lsidName="R. huashanensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" rank="species" species="huashanensis">
<emphasis id="1A8917BAE50FA5913817E3ECFED859EB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">R. huashanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
J.C. Wei, which differ by the umbilicate thallus, narrower ascospores, (7)8.5-12 
<normalizedToken id="98A9AEACDC34E765B912D139977C3F0D" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3.5-6 
<normalizedToken id="921E83F80CAC079EEEC95BEF30CF3A33" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
and the monophyllus thallus and black apothecia, respectively (
<bibRefCitation id="3446EB285467BC653B2CBBA12F1A89CE" author="Nash, III TH" journalOrPublisher="The Bryologist" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" refId="B11" refString="Nash, III TH, Ryan, BD, Gries, C, Bungartz, F, 2002. Lichen flora of the greater Sonoran Desert region, volume I. Lichen Unlimited, Arizona State University." title="Lichen flora of the greater Sonoran Desert region, volume I. Lichen Unlimited, Arizona State University." year="2002">Nash et al. 2002</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="FAC43DECD101749783A4440C794A1838" author="Wei, JC" journalOrPublisher="Acta Mycologica Sinica" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" pagination="207 - 213" refId="B17" refString="Wei, JC, 1984. A preliminary study of the lichen genus Rhizoplaca from China. Acta Mycologica Sinica 3: 207 - 213" title="A preliminary study of the lichen genus Rhizoplaca from China." volume="3" year="1984">Wei 1984</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="E9C5E8DC58191DB13C19DE81328BC024" authorityName="R. Sant" authorityYear="1984" baseAuthorityName="Nyl." class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Lecanoraceae" genus="Rhizoplaca" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Rhizoplaca subdiscrepans" order="Lecanorales" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="subdiscrepans">
<emphasis id="80AF9FEB322A97B5543345B38CC8753E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">Rhizoplaca subdiscrepans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nyl.) R. Sant. is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="928421650E5C65C4AA4301929DC8459B" genus="R." lsidName="R. callichroa" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" rank="species" species="callichroa">
<emphasis id="90347DCE29BAA5C4550CFD93684EDE2A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">R. callichroa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the squamulose thallus and orange apothecia, but differs in the very convex and smaller (0.3-1 mm) squamules and the narrower ascospores 7-12 
<normalizedToken id="D9B26B8BF0A5D96A41E8FE49CA0BFFE6" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3.5-5 
<normalizedToken id="11A4384FCBA12F69C1846142DEE1ADC5" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
<caption id="C838A12065C3D562C8C2F8E6D97C8E0E" doi="10.3897/mycokeys.66.39057.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/403704" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" start="Figure 4" startId="F4">
<paragraph id="A35A349CDC343603F8E334CFD4A09FBF" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">
<emphasis id="95035A6451C591E0286189860C8D1D38" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">Figure 4.</emphasis>
Maximum Likelihood phylogeny of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="03B60B2D42D0CC6290A3528CA6332B74" authorityName="Zopf" authorityYear="1905" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Lecanoraceae" genus="Rhizoplaca" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Rhizoplaca" order="Lecanorales" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="29A95E6CEDA80FF75D4F0FDD0DCC8DB1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">Rhizoplaca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and related genera of 
<taxonomicName id="F25E9E8426F10E705C7B04F4642A981C" authorityName="Zopf" authorityYear="1905" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Lecanoraceae" genus="Rhizoplaca" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="" order="Lecanorales" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="family">Lecanoraceae</taxonomicName>
, based on combined nrITS, nrLSU, RPB1, RPB2 and mtSSU. ML bootstrap value ≥ 70% and posterior probabilities ≥ 0.95 from the Bayesian analysis are given adjacent to nodes.
</paragraph>
